      <h1>Antenna</h1>
      <p class="lede">A paired sensory organ on a beeâ€™s head used for smell, taste, touch, temperature, humidity, and vibration detection.</p>

      <div class="grid cols-3">
        <section class="card" id="definition">
          <h2>Definition</h2>
          <p><strong>Antenna</strong> (plural: <em>antennae</em>): segmented feeler composed of a basal <em>scape</em>, a jointed <em>pedicel</em>, and a multi-segmented <em>flagellum</em>. Packed with sensory hairs and pits (sensilla) that detect odours, pheromones, CO<sub>2</sub>, humidity, temperature, and air movement.</p>
          <p class="muted">Pronunciation: /Ã¦n-<em>ten</em>-É™/ â€¢ /Ã¦n-<em>tiË</em>-niË/</p>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="function">
          <h2>What itâ€™s for</h2>
          <ul class="list">
            <li><strong>Smell & taste:</strong> recognising nectar sources, nestmate odours, alarm and queen pheromones.</li>
            <li><strong>Touch & vibration:</strong> close-up navigation on comb; detecting waggle-dance signals.</li>
            <li><strong>Climate sensing:</strong> maintaining brood temperature and humidity.</li>
